## Zero Trust

### Principle:
Never trust any user or device by default.

Always verify every request.

---

## Core Components
- MFA (Multi-factor authentication)
- Least privilege access
- Continuous monitoring
- Device verification

---

## Network Planes

### Data Plane
Handles actual traffic movement:
- Packet forwarding
- Filtering
- NAT
- Encryption

### Control Plane
Makes decisions:
- Routing rules
- Firewall policies
- Session management

### Management Plane
Used for configuration:
- Admin access
- System setup
- Monitoring tools

---

